<p>A complex number is an expression of the form <span class=3D"texhtml"><i=
>a</i> + <i>bi</i></span>, where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font=
-style:italic;">a</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-sty=
le:italic;">b</span> are real numbers, and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>i</i>=
</span> is an abstract symbol, the so-called imaginary unit, whose meaning =
will be explained further below. For example, <span class=3D"texhtml">2 + 3=
<i>i</i></span> is a complex number.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"referen=
