thbb {C} }"></span> is called an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A=
lgebraically_closed_field" title=3D"Algebraically closed field">algebraical=
ly closed field</a>. It is a cornerstone of various applications of complex=
 numbers, as is detailed further below.=20
There are various proofs of this theorem, by either analytic methods such a=
s <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liouville%27s_theorem_(complex_a=
nalysis)" title=3D"Liouville's theorem (complex analysis)">Liouville's theo=
rem</a>, or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topology" title=3D"Top=
