</p><p>In the 18th century complex numbers gained wider use, as it was noti=
ced that formal manipulation of complex expressions could be used to simpli=
fy calculations involving trigonometric functions. For instance, in 1730 <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abraham_de_Moivre" title=3D"Abraham =
