<p>In 1748, Euler went further and obtained <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Euler%27s_formula" title=3D"Euler's formula">Euler's formula</a> =
of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_analysis" title=3D"Comp=
lex analysis">complex analysis</a>:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-35" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_number#cite_note-35"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup>
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle e^{i\theta }=3D\cos \theta +i\sin \theta }">
