Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_analysis" ti=
tle=3D"Complex analysis">Complex analysis</a></div>
<p>The study of functions of a complex variable is known as <i><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_analysis" title=3D"Complex analysis">c=
omplex analysis</a></i> and has enormous practical use in <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Applied_mathematics" title=3D"Applied mathematics">=
applied mathematics</a> as well as in other branches of mathematics. Often,=
 the most natural proofs for statements in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Real_analysis" title=3D"Real analysis">real analysis</a> or even <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory" title=3D"Number theo=
ry">number theory</a> employ techniques from complex analysis (see <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number_theorem" title=3D"Prime numb=
er theorem">prime number theorem</a> for an example).=20
</p>
