 class=3D"texhtml">sinh</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml">cosh</span>, als=
o carry over to complex arguments without change. For the other trigonometr=
ic and hyperbolic functions, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Tangent_(function)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Tangent (function)"><=
span class=3D"texhtml">tan</span></a>, things are slightly more complicated=
, as the defining series do not converge for all complex values. Therefore,=
 one must define them either in terms of sine, cosine and exponential, or, =
equivalently, by using the method of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Analytic_continuation" title=3D"Analytic continuation">analytic continua=
tion</a>.
