<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Applications">Applications<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DComplex_numb=
er&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Applications"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<p>Complex numbers have applications in many scientific areas, including <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Signal_processing" title=3D"Signal p=
rocessing">signal processing</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Control_theory" title=3D"Control theory">control theory</a>, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electromagnetism" title=3D"Electromagnetism">ele=
ctromagnetism</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid_dynamics"=
 title=3D"Fluid dynamics">fluid dynamics</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Quantum_mechanics" title=3D"Quantum mechanics">quantum mechanic=
s</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cartography" title=3D"Carto=
graphy">cartography</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vibra=
tion#Vibration_analysis" title=3D"Vibration">vibration analysis</a>. Some o=
f these applications are described below.
</p><p>Complex conjugation is also employed in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Inversive_geometry" title=3D"Inversive geometry">inversive geo=
metry</a>, a branch of geometry studying reflections more general than ones=
 about a line. In the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_anal=
ysis_(electrical_circuits)" title=3D"Network analysis (electrical circuits)=
">network analysis of electrical circuits</a>, the complex conjugate is use=
d in finding the equivalent impedance when the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Maximum_power_transfer_theorem" title=3D"Maximum power transfe=
r theorem">maximum power transfer theorem</a> is looked for.
</p>
