_a_fortiori" title=3D"Argumentum a fortiori">A fortiori</a></i>, the same i=
s true if the equation has rational coefficients. The roots of such equatio=
ns are called <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_number" ti=
tle=3D"Algebraic number">algebraic numbers</a> =E2=80=93 they are a princip=
al object of study in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_nu=
mber_theory" title=3D"Algebraic number theory">algebraic number theory</a>.=
 Compared to <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span=
 class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: no=
ne;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displa=
