ightedge_constructions" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Compass and straight=
edge constructions">using only compass and straightedge</a> =E2=80=93 a pur=
ely geometric problem.
</p><p>Another example is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaus=
sian_integer" title=3D"Gaussian integer">Gaussian integers</a>; that is, nu=
mbers of the form <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> + <i>iy</i></span>, wher=
e <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> and <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> are intege=
rs, which can be used to classify <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Fermat%27s_theorem_on_sums_of_two_squares" title=3D"Fermat's theorem on sum=
s of two squares">sums of squares</a>.
